A command line utility for downloading and managing public pdf documents available from Ville de Montreal websites. 

The primary focus of this tool is to mine online public websites for information on land, water, and air contamination in the Montreal region. This is part of the open data project.

Project Website: http://remtl.ca
Project Sponsor: http://montrealouvert.net

Requirements:
- python 2.4 or greater (2.7.x recommended)
- BeautifulSoup html/xml parser available at http://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/

Basic Usage:

from a command line enter the following
> python remtlscraper.py -l    # list available region codes 
> python remtlscraper.py -h    # to display basic help 
> python remtlscraper.py -g 06 # to retrieve all data for a specified region code

 
